article.headline: Buffalo 64, Indiana State 51
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Mario Jordan scored 19 points and Yassin Idbihi added 10 to lead Buffalo to a 64-51 victory over Indiana State on Saturday. Buffalo (12-11) dominated the Sycamores from the field in the first half, shooting 47 percent (14-of-30), while Indiana State managed just 23 percent (5-of-22). The Bulls were 4-of-9 from 3-point range in the first half, while Indiana State (8-16) were 1-of-9 from beyond the arc. The Sycamores went the last 7:14 of the first half without a field goal and trailed 32-11. Ted Morris scored 13 points for Indiana State, while Ted Moss added 12 points and eight rebounds.
